abstract: >-
  Paper 59 of the Constructive Reverse Mathematics series. We formalize the
  p-adic precision bound N_M = v_p(det(1 - phi)) = v_p(1 - a_p + p) =
  v_p(#E(F_p)) for elliptic curves with good reduction. The Hasse bound
  implies #E(F_p) >= 1. Verified for 24 entries across 4 curves: 4 anomalous
  (N_M >= 1), 20 generic (N_M = 0). Max N_M = 2. "Axiom 5" is a theorem
  for geometric representations. Formalized in Lean 4 over Mathlib
  (762 lines, zero errors, zero sorry, zero custom axioms).
